# [project_name] Design System — Standards Overview

Nine specialized sub-rules handle specific file types and concerns. Cursor automatically activates the relevant sub-rule based on the file being edited.

## Sub-Rules Reference

| Sub-Rule | Activates On | Covers |
|---|---|---|
| `accessibility-guidelines` | `components/**/*.tsx` | WCAG AA, semantic HTML, ARIA roles, keyboard navigation, focus management |
| `base-components` | `components/ui/**/*.tsx`, `components/base/**/*.tsx` | BaseInput, BaseList, BaseListItem, InfoText, FieldLabel — APIs and accessibility |
| `component-internal-structure` | `components/**/*.tsx`, `components/**/*.module.scss` | Import order, `forwardRef`, CSS Module naming, sub-component organization |
| `layout-components` | `components/layout/**/*.tsx`, `components/**/*.tsx` | Box + Flex — props over CSS, spacing tokens, layout patterns |
| `new-component-implementation` | `components/**/*.tsx` | End-to-end workflow: types → component → styles → exports → tests → stories |
| `react-context` | Context files, providers, theme files | Context structure, Provider pattern, custom consumer hooks |
| `storybook-stories` | `*.stories.tsx`, `*.stories.ts` | CSF3 format, MDX docs, story conventions, decorators |
| `styling-conventions` | `*.module.scss`, `*.module.css`, style directories | SCSS Modules, `[style_package]` tokens, typography, anti-patterns |
| `color-token-management` | `packages/style/**/*` | Adding/modifying color tokens across all theme files, build process |

## Core Principles

### Tokens over raw values

```css
/* ✅ Use semantic tokens */
color: var(--primary-text-color);
margin-bottom: var(--space-8);

/* ❌ Never hardcode values in components */
color: #1a1a1a;
margin-bottom: 8px;
```

### Component anatomy

Every component requires: `ComponentName.tsx` + `ComponentName.types.ts` + `ComponentName.module.scss` + `index.ts` + `__tests__/` + `__stories__/`.

### Props over CSS for layout

Prefer `<Box>` and `<Flex>` from `@[project_folder]/core` over custom CSS for spacing, borders, and flexbox layouts.

### Accessibility first

All interactive components must be keyboard navigable, support ARIA attributes, and meet WCAG AA. See the `accessibility-guidelines` sub-rule.
